{{unref}}'''Chivatos''' is a Cuban term for those who cooperated with [[Fulgencio Batista|Batista]]'s Government denouncing people as revolutuionaries or against the regime. Those people had a good salary for do it and the most of them were arrested or executed when the [[Cuban Revolution|Revolution]] triumphed on [[January 1]] of [[1959]]. in modern times chivato is used in many spanish speaking countries, as cuba ofcourse where it originated, mexico, dominican republic, panama. this spanish term has a more open meaning now; as when you tell on someone, your a "chivato" 

